Business Brief -- BCE Inc.:
   Firm Negotiates to Increase
   Stake in SHL Systemhouse
In 1991, Systemhouse had a loss of C$19.9 million on
revenue of C$688.9 million. BCE, the parent of Bell Canada,
Canada's largest telephone utility, had earnings of C$1.33
billion in 1991 on sales of C$19.88 billion.
   Systemhouse said the proposal would involve Bell Canada
selling certain assets to Systemhouse for cash. Systemhouse
would operate Bell Canada's data center and related
operations. Bell Canada and Systemhouse would also establish
an enterprise to provide computer services to the
telecommunications industry.